The '''Santa Cruz shrikebill''' ('''''Clytorhynchus sanctaecrucis'''''), or '''Nendo shrikebill''', is a [[songbird]] [[species]] in the [[Family (taxonomy)|family]] [[Monarchidae]]. The Santa Cruz shrikebill was split from the [[black-throated shrikebill]] in 2008 but some authorities still consider it to be its [[subspecies]], ''C. n. sanctaecrucis''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/updates/archives/species-v1/|title=Species Version 1 « IOC World Bird List|website=worldbirdnames.org|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>

The Santa Cruz shrikebill is little-known species that has been very rarely sighted. It is [[endemic]] to the [[Solomon Islands]]. It is found on [[Nendo Island|Nendo]] in the [[Santa Cruz Islands]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

